FBIS3-20154 "drweu059_q_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 27 Mar 1994 TURKEY Gunman Killed in Mersin; Election-Related Clash TA2703093994 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 0905 GMT 27 Mar 94 TA2703093994 Ankara ANATOLIA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Mersin, Mar 26, (AA) -- A gunman was killed and a policeman was wounded in an overnight election-related clash in this southern city, police said on Saturday [26 March]. The clash started when gunmen, fleeing after throwing a bomb at the election office of the pro-Islamic Welfare [Prosperity] Party, fired on police, who urged them to surrender. One of the gunmen was killed, the others fled. Five other people, including a 12-year-old boy, were killed and 26 were wounded in the last couple of days in several assaults on party offices and candidates in the run-up to Sunday's nationwide municipal elections.
